## 33.2.25	2025-12-22

commit f2d11587fef7abdc2b7026a0af00c2149be28eb5
Author: C.J. Collier <cjac@google.com>
Date:   Sun Dec 21 04:57:03 2025 +0000

    feat(all): Reorganize project and introduce Protobuf Perl extension
    
    This commit restructures the repository, separating the Google::Auth library and introducing the in-development Protobuf Perl extension.
    
    **Project Structure Changes:**
    
    *   The original Google Auth library files previously in the root directory have been moved to the `google-auth/` subdirectory to better align with the CPAN module name `Google::Auth`.
    *   A copy of the `protobuf` C++ implementation has been added (not as a submodule) in the `protobuf/` directory, cloned from tag `33.2`. The Perl XS extension in `protobuf/perl/` will interface with this library.
    
    **Protobuf Perl Extension Development (protobuf/perl/):**
    
    This introduces the initial framework and implementation for the UPB-based Perl Protobuf XS extension. Development highlights include:
    
    *   **C Test Framework (protobuf/perl/t/c/):**
        *   Established a C-level testing system using an embedded Perl interpreter.
        *   `Makefile.PL` now manages C test compilation, including dynamic generation of rules from `c_test_config.json` and AddressSanitizer support.
        *   Common test helper functions are in `t/c/upb-perl-test.c` and `t/c/upb-perl-test.h`.
        *   Tests for various components are organized under `t/c/convert/`, `t/c/integration/`, and `t/c/protobuf/`.
    
    *   **Type Conversion Tests (protobuf/perl/t/c/convert/types/):**
        *   Test cases for `sv_to_upb` (Perl to C) and `upb_to_sv` (C to Perl) conversions cover all scalar types.
    
    *   **Build System (protobuf/perl/Makefile.PL):**
        *   Builds `libprotobuf_common.a` from UPB and other C/C++ sources.
        *   Generates `t/data/test_descriptor.bin` from `t/c/test.proto` using `protoc`.
        *   Manages dependencies and build order for C tests.
    
    *   **XS Layer (protobuf/perl/xs/):**
        *   Organized into subdirectories mirroring the Python UPB extension.
        *   Includes components for Arenas, Object Cache, Descriptors, and type conversion.
    
    *   **Perl Tests (`protobuf/perl/t/`):**
        *   Includes `t/030_sv_to_upb_errors.t` for testing error conditions in type conversions.
    
    **Current Status & Known Issues:**
    
    *   Core scalar type conversions between Perl and UPB C are passing in C-level tests.
    *   Minor memory leaks (8 bytes) are reported by ASan in some C tests (e.g., `t/c/convert/upb_to_sv`).
    *   Some C tests in `t/c/protobuf/` (arena, obj_cache) are not yet passing.
    *   ASan-specific tests require further tuning.
    
    This commit represents a significant step towards a functional Perl Protobuf extension.

